"{\"uid\": \"thestar.com-sports-olympic-champion-swimmer-cameron-mcevoy-breaks-the-50-meter-freestyle-world-record-article_655976dd-a3d8-582b-8147-440ade845368.html\", \"text\": \"  SHENZHEN, China (AP) - Olympic and world champion swimmer Cameron McEvoy has broken the men's 50-meter freestyle world record which had stood for 17 years.  FILE - Cameron McEvoy, of Australia, celebrates after winning the men's 50-meter freestyle final at the World Swimming Championships in Fukuoka, Japan, July 29, 2023. (AP Photo/David J. Phillip, File)  SHENZHEN, China (AP) - Olympic and world champion swimmer Cameron McEvoy has broken the men's 50-meter freestyle world record which had stood for 17 years.  The 31-year-old Australian posted a time of 20.88 seconds on Friday at the China Open in Shenzhen, taking 0.03 second off Brazilian C\\u00e9sar Cielo's previous mark.  Cielo set his world record of 20.91 during swimming's so-called \\\"super suit\\\" era in 2009. Those suits were later banned because they increased buoyancy and reduced drag, resulting in nearly 150 world records falling in 2009 before being prohibited in 2010.  \\\"I knew I had a chance to do a PB (personal best),\\\" McEvoy said. \\\"My old PB was 21.06, so maybe 20.99? But doing \\u206020.88 is unreal. It's crazy.\\\"  Cielo wasquick to congratulateMcEvoy on social media, tweeting: \\\"Congrats, Cam. Lightning fast swim! Incredible!\\\"  ___  AP sports:https://apnews.com/sports  Error!Sorry, there was an error processing your request.  There was a problem with the recaptcha. Please try again.  You may unsubscribe at any time. By signing up, you agree to ourterms of useandprivacy policy. This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Googleprivacy policyandterms of serviceapply.  Want more of the latest from us? Sign up for more at ournewsletter page.  The Associated Press  Error!There was an error processing your request.  There was a problem with the recaptcha. Please try again.  You may unsubscribe at any time. By